				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How important is agility?<a name="38936"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 7 04 6:26 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">Agility = AC pretty much. Put on a gear that gives you Raw AGI and no AC, and you will see your AC go up. Depending how much agi you have, it differs. 
<br />
LR is definately worthwhile. 
<br />
I would go for raw STA over AGI any day when looking for upgrades. Agi is nice, but sta/raw HP are the kings </span></blockquote>
<br />

<br />
There are 2 parts of your ac, 1) mitigation 2) avoidance.  Mitigation ac is based off spell buffs and gear ac.  Avoidance ac is based off agility from gear or from agi buffs.  The amount of agi it takes to increase 1ac varies depending on your class and level.
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://www.eatricezone.com/eq/avoidance01.jpg">
<br />

<br />
If you look at the above picture, you can see how the AC is broken down into the 2 components.  The beta EQ was setup to have both numbers displayed but they later changed it to just 1 AC figure.  Agi isn't as important as the other stats but it's not as worthless as everyone makes it out to be; they just don't fully understand the game mechanics.  With 305 agi, my avoidance ac gained is 20.  Every 10 avoidance ac will increase your (duh) avoidance 1% (miss / dodge / parry / riposte / block for mnk/bst).</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">[65 Deceiver]<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=362635" target="_blank">Derrict</a> (Halfling) <Retired></span></td>
