			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: How important is agility?<a name="41003"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 20 04 12:58 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>And there was also a parse log and summary done on www.thesteelwarrior.org that showed the effects of agility on misses factoring out armor class and ac effects. I cannot remember the exact number but I'm sure that someone here is registered there that can do a search on it (lazy bard here), I believe that mob misses increased 1% per 10 agility after the ac effects were factored out. Remember that this is not an additive sum, meaning 20 agility would not equal 2% more misses, but a fraction of that.
<br />

<br />
Example:
<br />

<br />
Mob hits 10000 times per unit of time X with agi Y
<br />

<br />
Agi increased by 10, hits reduced by 1%, mob now hits 9900 times.
<br />

<br />
Agi again increased by 10, mob hits 9900 times (minus 1% of 9900 or 99) = 9801 hits
<br />

<br />
Another agi increase of 10, mob hits 9801 hits minus 1% (98.1 rounded down to 98) = 9703 hits and so on.
<br />

<br />
Agi in itself isn't going to be a game breaker to invincibility, but rather another factor to think about when making YOUR character.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Ean
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
